  "text": "Patient characteristics of interest were sex, age, race, insurance status and concomitant diagnoses as defined above. Race was defined by White (referent), African American, Hispanic, Asian or Pacific Islander, and Native American. Insurance status was defined by Medicare (referent), Medicaid, private insurance, and other/self-pay/no charge. We defined the severity of co-morbid conditions using Deyo's modification of the Charlson co-morbidity index (CCI) (Supplementary Table S2 ). Thirty-one facilities were considered to be teaching hospitals if they have an American Medical Association-approved residency program, are a member of the Council of Teaching Hospitals, or have a full-time equivalent interns and residents to patient's ratio of ≥0. [CITATION_1] . HCUP NIS contains data on total charges for each hospital in the databases, which represents the amount that hospitals billed for services.",
